    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>stores a mapping from keys K to values V in one of two forms: 1) as dense map (vector) preferable when there are few missing keys in a range [0, endKey) 2) as hash map preferable when valid keys are a small subset of the range </para>
    </detaileddescription>
